    {
      "id": "569be99becc1c60edd03bf41a60f9a7990def016",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-01-20 20:16:30.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nin ofd_grant_check() {\n\n...\n                /* We can't check for already-mapped blocks here (make sense\n                 * when backend filesystem does not use COW) as it requires\n                 * dropping the grant lock.\n                 * Instead, we clear ~OBD_BRW_GRANTED and in that case we need\n                 * to go through and verify if all of the blocks not marked\n                 *  BRW_GRANTED are already mapped and we can ignore this error.\n                 */\n                rnb[i].rnb_flags &= ~OBD_BRW_GRANTED;\n                CDEBUG(D_CACHE,\"%s: cli %s/%p idx %d no space for %d\\n\",\n                                exp->exp_obd->obd_name,\n                                exp->exp_client_uuid.uuid, exp, i, bytes);\n...\n\n}\n\nand in ofd_preprw_write() {\n...\n                /* correct index for local buffers to continue with */\n                for (k = 0; k < rc; k++) {\n                        lnb[j+k].lnb_flags = rnb[i].rnb_flags;\n                        if (!(rnb[i].rnb_flags & OBD_BRW_GRANTED))\n                                lnb[j+k].lnb_rc = -ENOSPC;\n...\n}\n\nso in osd_write_prep(), we should check if the page has been granted, otherwise if this is not rewrite nor ldiskfs OSD, should we return the write with ENOSPC?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "2320fcaffaad44f7b287be175125c3c4f9267098",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2014-01-21 01:15:03.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.4/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/53944f8a-8236-11e3-94d9-52540035b04c).  Ran 21 tests.  1 tests failed: conf-sanity.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "f51cfe48e23ccdba154e111a33cfd35509a3ba17",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 104,
        "name": "Niu Yawei",
        "email": "yawei.niu@intel.com",
        "username": "niu",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-01-21 01:49:30.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nXiong, indeed. non-granted write can't allocate space reserved for grant, I was wrong about this before. But I still think sync write should consume grant, otherwise, space reserved for grant can't be used if there is only sync/direct write.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "58922607d697d307e7f9b1e38808977b39832e25",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 104,
        "name": "Niu Yawei",
        "email": "yawei.niu@intel.com",
        "username": "niu",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-01-21 04:30:56.000000000",
      "message": "Uploaded patch set 4.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "9751cf825d6f99fa1ac378dda6c50432e6f50f15",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 104,
        "name": "Niu Yawei",
        "email": "yawei.niu@intel.com",
        "username": "niu",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-01-21 04:34:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nGiven that the problem of sync write doesn't consume grant isn't that severe, I removed it from this patch. We may fix that later as an improvement.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "7f4000f3272f1337fc7516bda67b40d38d27fbef",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2014-01-21 04:39:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nany write  should go through grant reservation (on the client side or on the server side) and must fail if no enough space can be reserved. if, at some point, we have a mechanism to revoke all the grants, then we could switch to \"sync\" mode on the server where no grant reservation is needed, but this isn't the case currently.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "6e25fbf427092d211811affefbe9b34d3d71d0d7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
